The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 14 January is 168,330 (19,401 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 09 January, there were 10,480 new confirmed cases (1,207.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 02 January, there were 12,397 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 15% (1,917 fewer cases).
